<subSubSection id="226CB514CD71A58E41F32DE6972D2097" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B6A22CE78A30604B702815F74031D12" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09E0F77DAB37BF9D673399E5374824E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
The epithet 
<taxonomicName id="E3AF889EE008BBA2BD4886DF88EEB33C" authority="Wouters, 1983" authorityName="Munakata &amp; Tanaka &amp; Kakui" authorityYear="2022" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cavernocypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cavernocypris hokkaiensis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hokkaiensis">
<emphasis id="31329290C8A840CCF7795E63D858E1E6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Cavernocypris hokkaiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an adjective referring to the type locality, Hokkai-sawa Stream in Japan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="193603E4F2FAD28EF91B1AC86EE17386" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="new japanese name">
<paragraph id="BF17578B75BEA3BFFBC60F58CF3750AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">New Japanese name.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2ED1CE79F0D4885DA0C3A00E57E4DE9A" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="77DD6F6F412B20112E53A5F313BBFC14" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Shibare-doukutsu-kaimijinko</emphasis>
, referring to the habitat having low water temperature. 
<emphasis id="A9E956FA123E9FC38C75143B14EC2D06" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Shibare</emphasis>
is derived from the Japanese verb 
<emphasis id="558E0F89ABB8591C76BB0BD3252D29FA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">shibare-ru</emphasis>
(freeze), in a Hokkaido dialect; 
<emphasis id="2099FF8C7803DB54D6FB44A4ED740C5F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Doukutsu-kaimijinko</emphasis>
is the Japanese name for 
<taxonomicName id="CF4EB510B782F54A56009CC15AFEDFA5" authority="Wouters, 1983" authorityName="Wouters" authorityYear="1983" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cavernocypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cavernocypris" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="804E0098F546DA53D7EFAFDDA447E1AA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Cavernocypris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A013744F31D240167F6BB188A2362D5E" author="Tanaka, H" journalOrPublisher="Taxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="26 - 41" publicationUrl="https://www.jstage.jst.go.jp/article/taxa/38/0/38_KJ00009847304/_pdf" refId="B41" refString="Tanaka, H, Kotorii, H, Yokozawa, K, Wakabayashi, F, Kimoto, K, Sano, K, 2015. Distribution and occurrence of freshwater Ostracoda (Crustacea) from southwest region of Mt. Fuji. Taxa 38: 26 - 41, https://www.jstage.jst.go.jp/article/taxa/38/0/38_KJ00009847304/_pdf" title="Distribution and occurrence of freshwater Ostracoda (Crustacea) from southwest region of Mt. Fuji." url="https://www.jstage.jst.go.jp/article/taxa/38/0/38_KJ00009847304/_pdf" volume="38" year="2015">Tanaka et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7B399DBA9E54358CE3A9DB749D7116B8" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="type locality">
<paragraph id="F1E3C216ADF2CE7499EF89E14C780974" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7FD1036375AEAE892DF1DF32CFF860B0" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
Hokkai-sawa Stream, Daisetsuzan National Park, Hokkaido, Japan (Stn. 1: 
<geoCoordinate id="D5ABDAB2D9D765E5E18F795D0265425A" degrees="43" direction="north" minutes="41" orientation="latitude" precision="15" seconds="08" value="43.68556">43°41'08&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="51038BC17BEA61D80F6F495053BD42B8" degrees="142" direction="east" minutes="55" orientation="longitude" precision="15" seconds="28" value="142.92445">142°55'28&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C10F5647B89E91E0F4AFAF54DFDF928" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="3086814FDFD8EF75EAC0816B6A2EE4E8" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Holotype</emphasis>
: female, ICHUM-8247, one slide and one SEM stub, Stn.1, Hokkai-sawa Stream, riverbed sediment, 26 July 2021. 
<emphasis id="48D5F9B27BF92F097840E05955C8809B" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Paratypes</emphasis>
(five females): ICHUM-8248, 8249, one SEM stub and one slide for each; ICHUM-8250, 8251, one SEM stub; ICHUM-8252, one slide, voucher specimen for LC666823 (COI) and LC666824 (18S). Collection data for ICHUM-8249, 8252 are same as holotype; ICHUM-8248, 8251 were collected from Stn. 2 (
<geoCoordinate id="513D24E50645962426371D60FC5D297A" degrees="43" direction="north" minutes="41" orientation="latitude" precision="15" seconds="17" value="43.688057">43°41'17&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EDAFBD85A75C3EFCE78BD018268798E3" degrees="142" direction="east" minutes="54" orientation="longitude" precision="15" seconds="33" value="142.90916">142°54'33&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
) on 25 August 2020; ICHUM-8250 was collected from Stn. 1 on 25 August 2020. All individuals were collected by Mizuho Munakata.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B909AACCD5BA249A7E0DA17392747796" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="description">
<paragraph id="0D6DDE65F4C92F6E296A4FAAAF83EC14" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Description of females.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="283156F0D889B7F4404CDEF92A8A353D" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Measurements (in millimeters, except for ratios) of carapace and valves: LV-L, 0.59-0.61 (0.60, N=3); LV-H, 0.30-0.31 (0.31, N= 3); LV-H/LV-L, 0.50-0.51 (0.51, N=3); RV-L, 0.58-0.61 (0.60, N=3); RV-H, 0.29-0.31 (0.30, N=3); RV-H/RV-L, 0.50-0.51 (0.51, N=3); Ca-W, 0.25-0.26 (0.26, N=2); Ca-W/LV-L, 0.41-0.42 (0.42, N=2).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="93D8AABD3B870BF376AB43F62B7E7CF6" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
Carapace (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C5882CBFB9E6E35778AA111C5DA9B63B" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM images of carapaces and valves of female Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov. A. Paratype (ICHUM- 8250); B. Paratype (ICHUM- 8251); C, D. Paratype (ICHUM- 8248); E, F. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); G, H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Ventral and dorsal views of whole carapace; C, D. Outer views of left and right valves; E, F. Inner views of left and right valves; G, H. Inner dorsal views of left and right valves; dorsal portion of left valve broken. Arrows indicate anterior direction. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668859" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">2</figureCitation>
) translucent white, with black eye; outer surface smooth, with sparse, tiny setae but without shallow pits; widest point at about mid-length (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9E287C2FEF2006E73F68BF99C778C063" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM images of carapaces and valves of female Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov. A. Paratype (ICHUM- 8250); B. Paratype (ICHUM- 8251); C, D. Paratype (ICHUM- 8248); E, F. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); G, H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Ventral and dorsal views of whole carapace; C, D. Outer views of left and right valves; E, F. Inner views of left and right valves; G, H. Inner dorsal views of left and right valves; dorsal portion of left valve broken. Arrows indicate anterior direction. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668859" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">2A, B</figureCitation>
); LV overlapping RV at ventral margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3C4624795A3D1CAF2D0062C83D67DF1E" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM images of carapaces and valves of female Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov. A. Paratype (ICHUM- 8250); B. Paratype (ICHUM- 8251); C, D. Paratype (ICHUM- 8248); E, F. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); G, H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Ventral and dorsal views of whole carapace; C, D. Outer views of left and right valves; E, F. Inner views of left and right valves; G, H. Inner dorsal views of left and right valves; dorsal portion of left valve broken. Arrows indicate anterior direction. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668859" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">2A</figureCitation>
); no dorsal hump on LV (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E5659FBF2831385137089CD0916E9693" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM images of carapaces and valves of female Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov. A. Paratype (ICHUM- 8250); B. Paratype (ICHUM- 8251); C, D. Paratype (ICHUM- 8248); E, F. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); G, H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Ventral and dorsal views of whole carapace; C, D. Outer views of left and right valves; E, F. Inner views of left and right valves; G, H. Inner dorsal views of left and right valves; dorsal portion of left valve broken. Arrows indicate anterior direction. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668859" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">2B-D</figureCitation>
); outer list present in ventral margin of both valves (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="38AA38AB8161A1A9460E3937B18CD317" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM images of carapaces and valves of female Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov. A. Paratype (ICHUM- 8250); B. Paratype (ICHUM- 8251); C, D. Paratype (ICHUM- 8248); E, F. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); G, H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Ventral and dorsal views of whole carapace; C, D. Outer views of left and right valves; E, F. Inner views of left and right valves; G, H. Inner dorsal views of left and right valves; dorsal portion of left valve broken. Arrows indicate anterior direction. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668859" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="3030179C265B801521D7351D1B0F3C7A" doi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668859" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
