<paragraph id="F3E182692A3ED78E5AAA374F41B8CA21" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
LV (Figs 
<figureCitation id="A23FAFEBF3E3ACEC325EEB1BE30317E9" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM images of carapaces and valves of female Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov. A. Paratype (ICHUM- 8250); B. Paratype (ICHUM- 8251); C, D. Paratype (ICHUM- 8248); E, F. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); G, H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Ventral and dorsal views of whole carapace; C, D. Outer views of left and right valves; E, F. Inner views of left and right valves; G, H. Inner dorsal views of left and right valves; dorsal portion of left valve broken. Arrows indicate anterior direction. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668859" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">2C, E, G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B9E559039F740589F534B7586BBE9BEB" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov., female. A-G, I-L. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Inner views of left and right valves; C. Antennula; D. Antenna, outer view; E. Coxa of mandible; F. Mandible, inner view; G. Maxillula (vibratory plate omitted); H-J. Limbs 5 - 7; setules of distal setae on protopod and palp of limb 5 omitted; K. Uropodal ramus; L. Rake organ. Abbreviations: RO, Rome organ; WO, Wouters organ. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, B); 0.5 mm (C-K); 0.25 mm (L)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668860" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">3A</figureCitation>
) with greatest height at about mid-length; anterior and posterior margins evenly rounded; apex of anterior margin lower than mid-height of LV and slightly higher than apex of posterior margin; in inner view, calcified inner lamella on anterior and posterior margins well developed (Figs 
<figureCitation id="DBFD98348C00360338C1135890A1B6E6" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM images of carapaces and valves of female Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov. A. Paratype (ICHUM- 8250); B. Paratype (ICHUM- 8251); C, D. Paratype (ICHUM- 8248); E, F. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); G, H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Ventral and dorsal views of whole carapace; C, D. Outer views of left and right valves; E, F. Inner views of left and right valves; G, H. Inner dorsal views of left and right valves; dorsal portion of left valve broken. Arrows indicate anterior direction. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668859" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">2E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="EDAE8D76A595AD86FD9FDC86853C97B4" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov., female. A-G, I-L. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Inner views of left and right valves; C. Antennula; D. Antenna, outer view; E. Coxa of mandible; F. Mandible, inner view; G. Maxillula (vibratory plate omitted); H-J. Limbs 5 - 7; setules of distal setae on protopod and palp of limb 5 omitted; K. Uropodal ramus; L. Rake organ. Abbreviations: RO, Rome organ; WO, Wouters organ. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, B); 0.5 mm (C-K); 0.25 mm (L)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668860" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">3A</figureCitation>
); inner list present in ventral region (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6E96F5E56CF46C8455B8C10A1ADE48B0" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM images of carapaces and valves of female Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov. A. Paratype (ICHUM- 8250); B. Paratype (ICHUM- 8251); C, D. Paratype (ICHUM- 8248); E, F. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); G, H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Ventral and dorsal views of whole carapace; C, D. Outer views of left and right valves; E, F. Inner views of left and right valves; G, H. Inner dorsal views of left and right valves; dorsal portion of left valve broken. Arrows indicate anterior direction. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668859" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">2G</figureCitation>
); mid-ventral margin with inner triangular projection (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="959B424A05E3AEF8C6FE9ABD536CDBDD" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM images of carapaces and valves of female Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov. A. Paratype (ICHUM- 8250); B. Paratype (ICHUM- 8251); C, D. Paratype (ICHUM- 8248); E, F. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); G, H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Ventral and dorsal views of whole carapace; C, D. Outer views of left and right valves; E, F. Inner views of left and right valves; G, H. Inner dorsal views of left and right valves; dorsal portion of left valve broken. Arrows indicate anterior direction. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668859" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">2A, G</figureCitation>
). RV (Figs 
<figureCitation id="540BFF14870B82BA5F17D54118BF4366" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM images of carapaces and valves of female Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov. A. Paratype (ICHUM- 8250); B. Paratype (ICHUM- 8251); C, D. Paratype (ICHUM- 8248); E, F. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); G, H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Ventral and dorsal views of whole carapace; C, D. Outer views of left and right valves; E, F. Inner views of left and right valves; G, H. Inner dorsal views of left and right valves; dorsal portion of left valve broken. Arrows indicate anterior direction. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668859" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">2D, F, H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B22652A96BADDE7FB3C8D02E8269C44A" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov., female. A-G, I-L. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Inner views of left and right valves; C. Antennula; D. Antenna, outer view; E. Coxa of mandible; F. Mandible, inner view; G. Maxillula (vibratory plate omitted); H-J. Limbs 5 - 7; setules of distal setae on protopod and palp of limb 5 omitted; K. Uropodal ramus; L. Rake organ. Abbreviations: RO, Rome organ; WO, Wouters organ. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, B); 0.5 mm (C-K); 0.25 mm (L)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668860" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">3B</figureCitation>
) similar to LV in shape; inner list in ventral region absent (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="738B5129149CF290FB258CA9B4EF193C" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM images of carapaces and valves of female Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov. A. Paratype (ICHUM- 8250); B. Paratype (ICHUM- 8251); C, D. Paratype (ICHUM- 8248); E, F. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); G, H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Ventral and dorsal views of whole carapace; C, D. Outer views of left and right valves; E, F. Inner views of left and right valves; G, H. Inner dorsal views of left and right valves; dorsal portion of left valve broken. Arrows indicate anterior direction. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668859" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">2H</figureCitation>
). Two oblong mandibular muscle scars and four oblong adductor muscle scars on LV and RV (Figs 
<figureCitation id="9527E710BB36D853FDDBDBDCEEE64C18" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM images of carapaces and valves of female Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov. A. Paratype (ICHUM- 8250); B. Paratype (ICHUM- 8251); C, D. Paratype (ICHUM- 8248); E, F. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); G, H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Ventral and dorsal views of whole carapace; C, D. Outer views of left and right valves; E, F. Inner views of left and right valves; G, H. Inner dorsal views of left and right valves; dorsal portion of left valve broken. Arrows indicate anterior direction. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668859" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">2E, F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="01912656165F7A27E514B20CC9780471" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov., female. A-G, I-L. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Inner views of left and right valves; C. Antennula; D. Antenna, outer view; E. Coxa of mandible; F. Mandible, inner view; G. Maxillula (vibratory plate omitted); H-J. Limbs 5 - 7; setules of distal setae on protopod and palp of limb 5 omitted; K. Uropodal ramus; L. Rake organ. Abbreviations: RO, Rome organ; WO, Wouters organ. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, B); 0.5 mm (C-K); 0.25 mm (L)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668860" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">3A, B</figureCitation>
). Hinge adont.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC08D3E236B0893CCCBC385B0B378A16" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
An1 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5D6C2D87CC539B649240B575AD5B0292" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Cavernocypris hokkaiensis sp. nov., female. A-G, I-L. Holotype (ICHUM- 8247); H. Paratype (ICHUM- 8249); A, B. Inner views of left and right valves; C. Antennula; D. Antenna, outer view; E. Coxa of mandible; F. Mandible, inner view; G. Maxillula (vibratory plate omitted); H-J. Limbs 5 - 7; setules of distal setae on protopod and palp of limb 5 omitted; K. Uropodal ramus; L. Rake organ. Abbreviations: RO, Rome organ; WO, Wouters organ. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, B); 0.5 mm (C-K); 0.25 mm (L)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668860" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">3C</figureCitation>
) with seven podomeres. First podomere with one dorsal and two ventrodistal plumed setae and Wouters organ. Second podomere with dorsodistal seta reaching distal edge of third podomere and Rome organ. Third podomere with dorsodistal seta reaching distal edge of fourth podomere and ventrodistal seta extending beyond middle of fourth podomere. Fourth podomere with two dorsodistal setae of unequal length (longer one extending to distal edge of seventh podomere) and two ventrodistal setae reaching distal edge of sixth podomere. Fifth podomere with two dorsodistal setae of unequal length (longer one as long as podomeres 2-7) and two shorter ventrodistal setae. Sixth podomere with four outer distal setae as long as podomeres 1-7 and shorter inner distal seta. Seventh podomere with three distal setae of unequal length and aesthetasc ya (ca. 60% length of longest seta).
</paragraph>
<caption id="B14B65A2783B678CCD0E18FFD0FA57F2" doi="10.3897/zse.98.80442.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668860" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
